---
Jackal-headed humanoids who emerged from the mortuary-legal culture of Akh'enet, the
Khenari are psychopomps and death-administrators whose entire civilization is organized
around managing the threshold between life and death as a civic institution. Their
meticulous death-ledgers form the connective tissue of inheritance, water-rights, and
road-law. The Bellwind Collapse scattered their court families outward along caravan
routes, and Khenari communities now serve as notaries, estate administrators, and
death-record keepers wherever civilization requires incorruptible accuracy.
